panies and the addition of nine asphalt facilities to our portfolio will create opportunities for growth and increased shareholder value over the longterm” hurley saidblueknight energy partners is an oklahoma citybased midstream energy company that employs approximately  people in its tulsa office the company’s assets include crude oil storage approximately  million barrels of which are located in cushing pipeline transportation and oilfield services vehicles and asphalt product and residual fuel oil storageblueknight started in tulsa in  as a spinoff of semgroup lp but was acquired by vitol in  and underwent a name change charlesbank joined as a partner in  and the company’s headquarters moved to oklahoma city in as part of the acquisition deal announced tuesday ergon will contribute nine asphalt terminals it currently owns plus  million in cash to blueknight energy partnersthe nine terminals are located in kansas texas arizona alabama tennessee and mississippi and together include approximately  million barrels of storage capacityonce the transactions have closed blueknight will own a network of  asphalt terminals in  states with a combined capacity of  million barrels of asphalt and residual fuel oil storage  a month the new cost for doing business in tulsa if you care about business and this community its a small price to pay to be in the know for a limited time get a digital subscription for just  a month sign up now at tulsaworldcomsubscribe in return for the terminals and cash ergon will receive total consideration of approximately  million of preferred units and will acquire an aggregate of  million of common units for cashblueknight energy partners has also agreed to a  million repurchase of the majority of the series a preferred units currently controlled by vitol and charlesbankergon asphalt  emulsions chairman bill lampton said in a statement that ergon has had a longterm desire to help build a worldclass midstream master limited partnership and believes its investment in blueknight will help achieve that goallampton said the company has also identified two additional terminals that may be dropped into blueknight over the next couple of years“we believe that we are an ideal sponsor to help support and facilitate the growth of blueknight through our experience in the ownership of pipelines terminalling and storage facilities and other similar assets” lampton said “we expect blueknight to be a growth vehicle on its own with support from ergon” tags company blueknight energy partners lp ergon asphalt  emulsions inc businesshomepage ergon inc vicksburg mississippi semgroup blueknight gp holding llc ergon vitol charlesbank capital partners texas membership interests tennessee kansas blueknight energy partners lp residual fuel oil storage partner ceo transportation chairman alabama blueknight energy partners gp llc ergon asphalt emulsions inc mark hurley tulsa oklahoma city semgroup lp mississippi bill lampton arizona midstream energy crude oil storage asphalt product vitol holding bv × post a comment as emoticons smile beam wink sad cool innocent rolleyes whistling lol huh tongue love sleeping yawn unsure angry blink crying ohmy scared sleep sneaky tonguesmile thumbdown thumbup censored happybirthday ban spam offtopic batman ninja pirate alien comment text cancel post comment × report cancel report abuse × watch this discussion stop watching this discussion get an email notification whenever someone contributes to the discussion notifications from this discussion will be disabled cancel start watching stop watching  comments welcome to the discussion log in the tulsa world requires that you use your real first and last name on your account which will appear next to your comments if you see a questionable comment or a fake name click the report button next to the comment review the guidelines to post comments post a comment watch this discussion stop watching this discussion latest headlines man stabbed in chest late mon